cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.IT 

This paper deals with information-centric networking and in-network caching, which are primarily networking concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses game theory and optimization, which are relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The analysis of collaboration overhead and graph topologies is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
